# Status report layout and PDF

- **Single source of truth:** The only place to change layout or styling for both preview and PDF export is `components/StatusReportView.tsx`. The PDF is produced by client-side capture of that view (html2canvas + jsPDF in `lib/statusReportPdfCapture.ts`).
- Do not add a separate PDF-only layout or component. Any visual change must be made in StatusReportView so preview and exported PDF stay identical.
- **Timeline data** for a saved report comes from the report’s JSON **snapshot** (`lib/statusReportPdfData.ts`). To replace only the timeline with current project bars/markers after editing the Timeline tab, use **`POST /api/projects/[id]/status-reports/[reportId]/refresh-timeline`** (see `app/api/projects/[id]/status-reports/[reportId]/refresh-timeline/route.ts` and **Refresh timeline** in `StatusReportsTab.tsx`).
- **Meeting notes (HTML):** Rich text is sanitized in **`lib/meetingNotesHtml.ts`** (**`sanitize-html`**, allowlisted tags/attrs) before **`dangerouslySetInnerHTML`** in `StatusReportView`. Change allowlists there only; do not reintroduce **jsdom** / **isomorphic-dompurify** for this path (SSR + Turbopack production issues).
